---
source: src/core/certificate.rs
assertion: certificate verification uses real ed25519 signing for the certificate-signing surface
schema:
  verify: ee.certificate.verify.v1
  sign: ee.certificate.sign.v1
contracts:
  - signing binds payload hash bytes to an ed25519 keypair
  - forged signatures produced from public inputs fail verification
  - mutating a signed payload fails verification
  - deterministic test keys preserve stable acceptance coverage
  - content-hash attestations remain distinct from real signatures
evidence:
  - ee.ed25519.v1
  - certificate signing round-trip tests
  - forged signature rejection tests
  - mutated payload rejection tests
  - adversarial public-input reproduction test
